OMV Petrom First-Quarter Output Increases 0.5%; Gas Sales Fall

-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 
2011-04-28T06:22:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/omv-petrom-first-quarter-output-increases-0-5-gas-sales-fall.html
OMV Petrom SA (SNP) , Romania’s largest
energy company, said first-quarter oil and natural-gas output
rose 0.5 percent from the previous three months.  Output advanced to 186,000 barrels of oil equivalent a day
from 185,000 barrels in the fourth quarter last year, the
Bucharest-based company’s majority owner  OMV AG (OMV)  said today in a
statement.  Gas sales volume dropped to 1.46 billion cubic meters from
1.58 billion cubic meters the previous quarter, according to the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
